 What Where Find Jobs Advanced Job Search This job has expired on Indeed Reasons could include: the employer is not accepting applications, is not actively hiring, or is reviewing applications Design Verification Engineer Hewlett Packard Enterprise Austin, TX 78730 Hewlett Packard Enterprise advances the way people live and work. We bring together the brightest minds to create breakthrough technology solutions, helping our customers make their mark on the world. 
 
At HPC, MCS and Hewlett Packard Labs, we focus on cutting edge, high-performance, high-scale customer solutions serving a wide range of industries and end-users. Our organization includes High Performance Computing (HPC), Artificial Intelligence (AI), Mission Critical Solutions (MCS), Edgeline, Moonshot and Hewlett Packard Labs. 
As a Design Verification Engineer at HPE, you will have the opportunity to be part of a world class team, designing High Performance Computing (HPC) networking ASICs that are the building blocks of the Slingshot interconnect. In this role you will be responsible for all phases of pre-silicon design verification, including design verification methodology, test-plan development, writing tests, creating stimulus and checkers, coverage closure, and sign off reviews. 
Knowledge and Skills: 
Develop testbenches using System Verilog and the UVM methodology for industry leading high performance ASICs 
Contribute to bus functional models that drive and monitor stimulus. 
Add features to scoreboards and checkers to verify functional behavior. 
Write constrained-random tests. 
Write and analyze functional coverage. 
Follow the teams design verification methodology. 
Triage regression failures and identify logic bugs. 
Collaborate and communicate with management regarding design status, project progress, and issue resolution. 
Participate as a member of our team to develop reliable, cost effective and high quality solutions for VLSI products. 
Preferred knowledge and skills: 
Ability to work well in a distributed team environment. 
Good understanding of OVM and UVM methodologies. 
Good analytical and problem solving skills. 
Understanding of design for VLSI components, integrated circuitry, architectures and algorithms. 
Knowledge of Verilog and System Verilog, Coursework in VLSI design or VLSI concepts. 
Good written and verbal communication skills; Mastery in English. 
About You: 
Bachelor's or Master's degree in Electrical Engineering, Computer Engineering, Computer Science or equivalent. 
0-5 years of experience in ASIC design, verification or physical design. 
